data.name: lblStructureHowToStartContent
data.value:
Most decision projects have the following 3 elements:
  1. Decision %%Objectives%%: These determine how to accomplish the Goal (desired end-result)
  2. %%Alternatives%%: These are the possible options that you are choosing among
  3. Evaluators: The people who evaluate the priority of %%Objectives%%, and preference of %%Alternatives%% for each %%Objective%%.
For example, if you are choosing a rental car for your next business trip, you might structure a model like this: The decision goal is: "Choosing a rental car for a business trip" The Decision %%Objectives%% might be:
  • Comfort
  • Price
  • Availability with Preferred Provider
The Alternatives might be:
  • Compact
  • Sedan
  • SUV
The Evaluators could be the team that's traveling with you, or it could be just you. You can always evaluate the decision project for yourself, without adding additional evaluators.

To get started defining Objectives and Alternatives, mouse over the highlighted area on the main page and click the right mouse button.
